HEADWORD: Mackinaw
<hw>Mack"i*naw</hw>.
}</mhw><ety>[From <ets>Mackinac</ets>, the State of Michigan, where
blankets and other stores were distributed to the Indians.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A thick blanket formerly in common use in the western
part of the United States.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a heavy woolen cloth heavily napped and felted,
often with a plaid design.</def> <wns>[wns=4]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

